title: Indiana Firm Recalls Frozen Chicken Pot Pie Products That May Contain Foreign Materials
summary: January 20, 2010 - Park 100 Foods, Inc., a Kokomo, Ind., establishment, is recalling approximately 19,200 pounds of frozen chicken pot pie products that may contain foreign materials, the U.S. Department of Agriculture's Food Safety and Inspection Service (FSIS) announced today. The following product is...
impacted_products: 2.5-pound cartons of "Market Day®, CHICKEN POT PIE, Made With All White Chicken Meat."
